  "text": "The approach to constructing and manipulating heterogeneous specifications that we use was outlined in Section 2.3. We use predicative refinement rules on heterogeneous specifications taken from [CITATION_1] . These refinement rules are syntactically very similar to standard predicative refinement rules, and they provably maintain the key properties of predicative refinement, e.g., the ability to refine specifications by parts and steps [CITATION_2] . It is these properties that can make the heterogeneous approach to proving time constraints very attractive.",
